rom political scientists across Canada, Big City Elections in Canada provides a data-driven overview of each election while also highlighting the more general lessons that they teach us about municipal politics and voting behaviour. The chapters in this book make substantial empirical and theoretical contributions to the voting behaviour and urban political science subfields and will appeal to students, journalists, and engaged citizens who are interested in learning more about municipal elections in their cities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLocal electionszCanada. 0aMunicipal governmentzCanada. 0aVoting researchzCanada. 0aVotingzCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh  aCanada.  aelections.  alocal elections.  amunicipal elections.  amunicipal politics.  apolitical behaviour.1 aAnderson, Cameron D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreux, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBélanger, Éric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCouture, Jérôme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaoust, Jean-François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLucas, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLucas, Jack, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMatthews, J. Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGregor, R. Michael , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcgregor, R. Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Aaron A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPickup, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb